#META# contentSummary: A brief legal query (*istiftā*) regarding whether the seller has the right to compel the buyer 's representative to appear before the buyer (the nephew) in order to renew (*tajdīd*) the annulment of the transaction. The response rules that the seller cannot force the representative to do so.
